        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Do I think kids should be FORCED to recite the pledge of allegiance before school in the mornings?</P><P>YES</P><P>Do I think the phrase 'under god' should be removed from the pledge?</P><P>YES!!!</P><P>Im all for patriotism, and being grateful for all the freedoms living in the greatest nation the world has ever seen (by any standard) grants its citizens.</P><P>BUT. I think religion is stupid, and dangerous. The sooner it falls by the wayside, thrown upon the heap of lies and myths no longer believed in, the better.</P><P>I personally find the belief in a god utterly ridiculous, and completely unprovable. I think religion had its place in human development....about 400 years ago. We now have much better tools to define and describe our universe. Reason and logic. Renaissance anyone?</P><P>Anyway, I am not telling you to stop believing. Believe whatever you want. Believe in god, believe in santa claus, whatever you need to get you through the day. But it needs to be completely and utterly separate from the state, in every way.</P><P>Why should my child have to be singled out, alienated, and branded some sort of objector/protestor/unamerican simply because I refuse to force him/her to believe in some invisible all-powerful entity? Take the damn line out of the pledge. Why is that so offensive to all you religious types? The line wasn't a part of the original pledge, so what's the big deal?</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
